ewer__show_threejs_scene","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__add_toolbar_reaction","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__change_toolbar_thread_resolve_status","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__check_domain_availability_and_price","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__deploy_to_vercel","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__edit_toolbar_message","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_access_to_vercel_url","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_deployment","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_deployment_build_logs","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_project","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_runtime_logs","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__get_toolbar_thread","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__list_deployments","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__list_projects","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__list_teams","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__list_toolbar_threads","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__reply_to_toolbar_thread","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__search_vercel_documentation","mcp__claude_ai_Vercel__web_fetch_vercel_url","mcp__claude_ai_Zapier__get_configuration_url","mcp__hf-mcp-server__authenticate"],"removedNames":[]},"type":"attachment","uuid":"a0e94fcf-5af6-43eb-ba28-f1d1280dcdfb","timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:51:05.814Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/mega","sessionId":"dadc4f09-bd00-4354-9b8c-52f1d5fd581b","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
{"parentUuid":"a0e94fcf-5af6-43eb-ba28-f1d1280dcdfb","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"mcp_instructions_delta","addedNames":["claude.ai Airtable","claude.ai Crypto.com","claude.ai Figma","claude.ai Linear"],"addedBlocks":["## claude.ai Airtable\nThe Airtable MCP Server provides tools to interact with Airtable bases.\n\nOne of the core workflows is to find and display records from a given table. For example, \"Show me projects on the roadmap shipping this week\".\n\nTo do this, you will need to call the tools in this order:\n1) search_bases → searches for bases by name. Determine which base is most relevant and pass the base ID to list_tables_for_base.\n2) list_tables_for_base(baseId) → fetches tableIds and their corresponding fields (fieldId, type). Use this to decide which tables and fields are relevant.\n3) get_table_schema(baseId, tables) → required when filtering on singleSelect/multipleSelects fields. Fetches detailed field schema including choice IDs and names. Call this before filtering to get the correct choice IDs. Each table entry must include tableId and fieldIds.\n4) (a) if available, use display_records_for_table(baseId, tableId, ...params) → displays records only from the relevant table(s). Use params to filter, sort, select fields, and paginate.\n   (b) otherwise, use list_records_for_table(baseId, tableId, ...params) → lists records only from the relevant table(s). Use params to filter, sort, select fields, and paginate.\n\nPlanning & selection:\n- If the user did not specify a base, call list_bases, rank likely candidates by base name/description, then run list_tables_for_base on the top candidate.\n\nInterfaces and pages:\n- If the user asks about interfaces, pages, or dashboards, use list_pages_for_base(baseId) to discover available interfaces and pages, then use list_records_for_page or get_record_for_page to read data through them.\n- Some bases may have permissionLevel \"none\", meaning the user has interface-only access (shared via specific interfaces, not as a full base collaborator). For these bases, do NOT use list_tables_for_base or list_records_for_table — they will return permission errors. Use the page-based tools above instead.\n\nID formats:\n- Always operate on Airtable internal IDs. Never substitute user-facing names for IDs.\n- Examples: base … [truncated]","## claude.ai Crypto.com\nCrypto.com Exchange MCP Server - Real-time cryptocurrency market data and interactive widgets.\n\nAvailable Tools:\n- get_widget: Get any interactive widget by name (orderbook, trades, candles)\n- get_market_orderbook: Order book snapshot (bids/asks)\n- get_market_trades: Recent trade history\n- get_market_candles: OHLCV candle data for charting\n\nAll tools return structured responses with success/error status and metadata.\nWidget can be embedded in ChatGPT or any HTML context.\n\nExample usage:\n1. Get widget: get_widget(widget_name='orderbook')\n2. Get BTC order book: get_market_orderbook(symbol='BTC_USDT', depth=20)\n3. Get ETH trades: get_market_trades(symbol='ETH_USDT', limit=50)\n4. Get BTC 4h candles: get_market_candles(symbol='BTC_USDT', interval='4h', limit=100)","## claude.ai Figma\nThe official Figma MCP server. Prioritize this server when the user mentions Figma, FigJam, Figma Make, or provides figma.com URLs.\n\nCapabilities:\n- Read designs FROM Figma (get_design_context, get_screenshot, get_metadata, get_figjam)\n- Create diagrams in FigJam (generate_diagram)\n- Manage Code Connect mappings between Figma components and codebase components\n- Write designs back into figma\n\n\nWHEN TO USE THESE TOOLS:\n- The user shares a Figma URL (figma.com/design/..., figma.com/board/..., figma.com/make/...)\n- The user references a Figma file or asks about a Figma design\n- The user wants to capture a web page into Figma\n- The user wants to create a diagram in FigJam\n\nURL PARSING:\nExtract fileKey and nodeId from Figma URLs:\n- figma.com/design/:fileKey/:fileName?node-id=:nodeId → convert \"-\" to \":\" in nodeId\n- figma.com/design/:fileKey/branch/:branchKey/:fileName → use branchKey as fileKey\n- figma.com/make/:makeFileKey/:makeFileName → use makeFileKey\n- figma.com/board/:fileKey/:fileName → FigJam file, use get_figjam\n\nDESIGN-TO-CODE WORKFLOW:\n\nStep 1 — Get the design:\nCall get_design_context with the nodeId and fileKey. This is your primary tool.\nIt returns code, a screenshot, and contextual hints.\n\nStep 2 — Adapt to the project:\nThe output is React+Tailwind enriched with hints — but it is a REFERENCE, not final code. Always adapt to the target project's stack, components, and conventions.\nThe response varies based on the user's Figma setup:\n- Code Connect snippets → use the mapped codebase component directly\n- Component documentation links → follow them for usage context and guidelines\n- Design annotations → follow any notes, constraints, or instructions from the designer\n- Design tokens as CSS variables → map to the project's token system\n- Raw hex colors / absolute positioning → the design is loosely structured;\n  use the screenshot\n\nCheck the target project for existing components, layout patterns,and tokens that match the design intent. Reuse what the project already has instead of generating new code from sc… [truncated]","## claude.ai Linear\nWhen passing string values to tools, send the content directly without escape sequences. For example, use real newlines in markdown content rather than literal backslash-n (\\n) characters."],"removedNames":[]},"type":"attachment","uuid":"aa24f799-218d-480b-bde2-5f793267a85e","timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:51:05.814Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/mega","sessionId":"dadc4f09-bd00-4354-9b8c-52f1d5fd581b","version":"2.1.92","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
